-- Greece Ratings Cut to Junk by S&P
-- Greg Chang
-- 2010-04-27T15:24:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/greece-ratings-cut-to-junk-by-s-p.html

          
          
             Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services
lowered its long- and short-term sovereign credit ratings on
Greece to ‘BB+’ and ’B’, respectively, from ’BBB+’ and ’A-2’.
The outlook is negative.  
 Credit-default swaps on Greek government debt rose 104
basis points to a record 814, according to CMA DataVision
prices.  
          
          


  


        